WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:02.919
<i>- Previously on
"Superman and Lois"...</i>

00:02.920 --> 00:04.754
- Where's Elizabeth now?

00:04.755 --> 00:05.922
- The only person
who knows that is Sam Lane.

00:05.923 --> 00:07.716
- Sorry, General.

00:07.717 --> 00:09.217
<i>- Either you give me
Elizabeth now,</i>

00:09.218 --> 00:10.927
<i>or I can send something
that doesn't need a gun.</i>

00:10.928 --> 00:13.054
- [growling]

00:13.055 --> 00:15.056
<i>- Tell me where Elizabeth is.</i>

00:15.057 --> 00:16.975
- I promised to protect her.

00:16.976 --> 00:18.101
<i>- Where is she?</i>

00:18.102 --> 00:19.686
- I gave her my word.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.563
[bone snaps]

00:21.564 --> 00:23.773
<i>- If Kal is to return,
it will take many days.</i>

00:23.774 --> 00:25.775
<i>And even then,
I have concerns.</i>

00:25.776 --> 00:27.862
[heartbeat thumping]

00:30.364 --> 00:32.949
- You crashed?
- This was just a fluke.

00:32.950 --> 00:35.201
- Pretty soon you're gonna be
back in the public eye.

00:35.202 --> 00:37.287
I'm gonna miss having you
all to myself.

00:37.288 --> 00:39.289
- Well, I'm here now.

00:39.290 --> 00:42.334
[phone vibrates]

00:45.713 --> 00:48.590
[thunder rumbles]

00:48.591 --> 00:49.966
- Couldn't do it yourself,

00:49.967 --> 00:53.678
so you had the sheriff
serve me these?

00:53.679 --> 00:56.222
- I'll give you
a ring tomorrow, Kat.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.932
- Just tell me what you want.

00:57.933 --> 01:00.018
- Well, I think the divorce
papers make that pretty clear.

01:00.019 --> 01:01.561
- Why are you being
like this, Erica?

01:01.562 --> 01:02.979
- Oh, are you not
feeling respected,

01:02.980 --> 01:04.773
like you don't have a say
in anything?

01:04.774 --> 01:06.816
Well, welcome to the last
14 years of our marriage.

01:06.817 --> 01:08.193
- Don't put this all on me.

01:08.194 --> 01:09.944
- You were never here.

01:09.945 --> 01:12.322
You didn't even try
and connect with me.

01:12.323 --> 01:13.490
- We went to therapy.

01:13.491 --> 01:14.908
- Once,

01:14.909 --> 01:17.452
and you said
that it wasn't for you.

01:17.453 --> 01:19.704
Everything has to be for you.

01:19.705 --> 01:24.501
Can you not see
how lonely I am?

01:24.502 --> 01:28.797
How desperate I am for even
a scrap of attention from you?

01:28.798 --> 01:32.008
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

01:32.009 --> 01:34.636
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:34.637 --> 01:37.222
- It's not that simple.

01:37.223 --> 01:40.725
You don't know
what I went through growing up.

01:40.726 --> 01:43.812
- But I'm your wife.

01:43.813 --> 01:48.525
And you never let me in, ever.

01:48.526 --> 01:51.986
You act like you're this
big, tough genius.

01:51.987 --> 01:55.865
But really, you are still
that angry little boy

01:55.866 --> 01:58.786
from South Metropolis
whose mother hurt him.

02:01.205 --> 02:05.668
She has made it impossible
for you to love anyone...

02:07.461 --> 02:09.004
Including your daughter.

02:11.257 --> 02:12.215
<i>[music darkens]</i>

02:12.216 --> 02:13.758
- That's not fair.

02:13.759 --> 02:17.304
- No. To her, it isn't.

02:19.473 --> 02:22.517
You know the real tragedy?

02:22.518 --> 02:26.437
One day, Elizabeth will
come to you

02:26.438 --> 02:28.773
and beg you for your love.

02:28.774 --> 02:31.401
And you will push her away,

02:31.402 --> 02:34.112
just like you did to me.

02:34.113 --> 02:37.407
From now on, only contact me
through my lawyer.

02:37.408 --> 02:40.493
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:40.494 --> 02:42.370
<i>- Lex.</i>

02:42.371 --> 02:44.330
Lex, did you hear me?

02:44.331 --> 02:47.083
We're getting closer
to finding Elizabeth.

02:47.084 --> 02:48.877
- I heard you.

02:48.878 --> 02:53.089
- The DOD figured out a way
around facial recognition.

02:53.090 --> 02:55.216
Milton's looking
into a fix for that.

02:55.217 --> 02:58.636
- Tell him he has
until the end of the week.

02:58.637 --> 03:01.139
I'm headed back to Smallville.

03:01.140 --> 03:02.849
- Tonight? For what?

03:02.850 --> 03:04.767
- To take care of this.

03:04.768 --> 03:07.770
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:07.771 --> 03:13.234
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:13.235 --> 03:16.237
<i>[heroic music]</i>

03:16.238 --> 03:19.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:20.242 --> 03:22.035
<i>- I'm sure
Luthor has seen the news.</i>

03:22.036 --> 03:23.661
He knows you're alive, Clark.

03:23.662 --> 03:24.954
It's only a matter of time
before he sends

03:24.955 --> 03:26.873
that thing after you again.

03:26.874 --> 03:29.500
- I know.
We just need to find a way

03:29.501 --> 03:31.294
to make sure
that doesn't happen.

03:31.295 --> 03:32.420
- What way?

03:32.421 --> 03:34.005
The DOD can't help.

03:34.006 --> 03:36.591
Lieutenant Jones went AWOL
after shooting my dad.

03:36.592 --> 03:38.468
And without him,
they have zero evidence

03:38.469 --> 03:40.261
tying Luthor
to my father's death,

03:40.262 --> 03:41.930
not to mention yours.

03:41.931 --> 03:44.557
- OK, OK, I know this is
gonna sound a little crazy,

03:44.558 --> 03:48.353
but what if--
what if we just talk to him?

03:48.354 --> 03:50.396
- Talk to Luthor?

03:50.397 --> 03:51.814
- Yeah, face-to-face.

03:51.815 --> 03:54.567
- And say what?
"Let's call it even"?

03:54.568 --> 03:56.027
He killed my father.

03:56.028 --> 03:58.279
He killed you
and so many others.

03:58.280 --> 04:01.908
Talking to that psychopath
is a waste of time.

04:01.909 --> 04:04.369
- I'm just saying,
he blames us for being

04:04.370 --> 04:06.621
separated from his daughter
for 17 years, right?

04:06.622 --> 04:08.039
- So?

04:08.040 --> 04:11.250
- OK, look, I know
it's a Hail Mary, but--

04:11.251 --> 04:13.169
I don't know, maybe it's like
my mom used to say.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.671
Sometimes the only way
to reach someone

04:14.672 --> 04:16.255
is through their heart, so...

04:16.256 --> 04:18.132
- If you want
to talk to him, fine.

04:18.133 --> 04:20.259
But we need to attack this
on both fronts.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.636
So I'm gonna stay here

04:21.637 --> 04:23.805
and go through my dad's
old DOD files.

04:23.806 --> 04:25.974
Maybe I'll find
a second Hail Mary.

04:25.975 --> 04:28.936
- OK, well, wish me luck.

04:35.734 --> 04:38.653
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:38.654 --> 04:45.660
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:45.661 --> 04:47.412
- Total jackpot.

04:47.413 --> 04:49.038
[laughter]

04:49.039 --> 04:51.082
- I mean, he's not wrong.

04:51.083 --> 04:53.710
- Are you sure there's,
like, enough in there, or...

04:53.711 --> 04:55.545
- I literally bought
everything they had.

04:55.546 --> 04:57.046
- Dude,
you're not gonna make it

04:57.047 --> 04:58.381
out of the 4th of July
with all your fingers.

04:58.382 --> 05:01.009
- OK, you know what? Look.
- [laughs]

05:01.010 --> 05:02.969
- We are living in weird times.

05:02.970 --> 05:05.346
We all witnessed the world
almost end twice.

05:05.347 --> 05:08.224
And then some monster shows up
and nearly kills Superman.

05:08.225 --> 05:09.809
You know,
if he can barely survive,

05:09.810 --> 05:11.352
then no one's safe.

05:11.353 --> 05:14.814
So might as well live it up
while we still can.

05:14.815 --> 05:17.108
- Jeez, stop being
such a doomsdayer.

05:17.109 --> 05:18.818
- Candice is still coming, right?

05:18.819 --> 05:20.987
- Yeah,
she should be here soon.

05:20.988 --> 05:22.655
- She's been texting all week.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.574
She's probably thinking you're
gonna flake on her again.

05:24.575 --> 05:25.867
- It was one time.

05:25.868 --> 05:27.744
[laughter]
- Dude, just be careful.

05:27.745 --> 05:29.871
You know, she--
she might just dump you

05:29.872 --> 05:31.581
for one of those Wichita boys.

05:31.582 --> 05:32.832
[laughter]
- Oh, shut up.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.542
- Come on,
let's go get the keg.

05:34.543 --> 05:36.462
- [laughs]

05:37.379 --> 05:40.423
- Hey, um,
sorry about Wellnitz.

05:40.424 --> 05:43.092
- Oh, I'm not worried
about Candice.

05:43.093 --> 05:45.344
- Oh, no,
that's not what I meant.

05:45.345 --> 05:50.391
Um, look, I was there
the night that that thing came,

05:50.392 --> 05:51.976
and I saw what happened.

05:51.977 --> 05:55.563
- You mean to Superman?

05:55.564 --> 05:57.899
- Yeah, to your dad.

05:57.900 --> 06:00.234
- What? No.
- Denise.

06:00.235 --> 06:02.528
- No, it's OK.
I'm not gonna say anything.

06:02.529 --> 06:06.365
It just--it just really sucks

06:06.366 --> 06:07.992
that you had
to go through that.

06:07.993 --> 06:10.703
And, um, I'm just--

06:10.704 --> 06:13.498
I'm really glad that he's OK.

06:13.499 --> 06:16.210
- Yo, come on. Let's go.

06:17.544 --> 06:21.798
- Anyways, I will
see you guys tonight.

06:21.799 --> 06:28.805
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:28.806 --> 06:30.681
<i>- After multiple sources
confirmed</i>

06:30.682 --> 06:33.142
<i>seeing the Man of Steel
flying to and from</i>

06:33.143 --> 06:36.521
<i>the Mall of Metropolis,
speculation about how Superman</i>

06:36.522 --> 06:38.481
<i>survived after his scare--</i>

06:38.482 --> 06:41.609
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:41.610 --> 06:47.366
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:53.497 --> 06:56.415
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:56.416 --> 07:02.964
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:02.965 --> 07:05.217
- Superman.

07:07.344 --> 07:08.512
Or is it Clark?

07:11.598 --> 07:14.475
I guess it depends on
which costume you're wearing.

07:14.476 --> 07:15.685
- Can we talk?

07:15.686 --> 07:17.396
- How did Lois do it?

07:20.941 --> 07:23.318
Bring you back from the dead.

07:25.612 --> 07:28.781
I'm assuming it's...

07:28.782 --> 07:31.576
some alien technology.

07:31.577 --> 07:33.661
- That's not why I'm here.

07:33.662 --> 07:35.204
- Then you're wasting my time.

07:35.205 --> 07:38.291
- I came to speak to you
as a father.

07:38.292 --> 07:40.084
Whatever you're doing
here in Smallville,

07:40.085 --> 07:41.919
I'm asking for it to stop.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.713
- That's not up to you.

07:43.714 --> 07:45.006
- You're harassing my family.

07:45.007 --> 07:46.924
- Because you destroyed mine.

07:46.925 --> 07:48.968
- We were wrong.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.052
And I regret that.

07:50.053 --> 07:51.304
- I don't want your apology.

07:51.305 --> 07:53.097
- Either way, you have it.

07:53.098 --> 07:55.266
What happened to your daughter,

07:55.267 --> 07:58.394
having her father taken away,

07:58.395 --> 07:59.979
it should never happen
to anyone.

07:59.980 --> 08:01.439
- And on that, we agree.

08:01.440 --> 08:03.357
- But it doesn't justify
what you're doing.

08:03.358 --> 08:05.902
Going after us won't give you
that time back with her.

08:05.903 --> 08:07.445
Nothing will.

08:07.446 --> 08:09.906
You have to find
another way forward.

08:09.907 --> 08:13.034
- There is no other way.

08:13.035 --> 08:15.828
Do you even know
what it feels like to suffer?

08:15.829 --> 08:20.291
- Lex, some part of you

08:20.292 --> 08:23.669
has to want this cycle of anger
to end.

08:23.670 --> 08:25.922
- Is that what you came back
to life to tell me,

08:25.923 --> 08:28.132
that there's something better
after all of this,

08:28.133 --> 08:32.178
if only I can find
the goodness in my heart?

08:32.179 --> 08:34.889
- I won't let you
hurt my family.

08:34.890 --> 08:39.769
- Enjoy the time you have left.

08:39.770 --> 08:42.105
It's running out.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.901
[scoffs]

08:46.902 --> 08:54.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:55.619 --> 08:57.745
[whooshing]

08:57.746 --> 09:01.415
- Are you sure you don't want
a lawyer present, Mr. Luthor?

09:01.416 --> 09:04.210
- I'm good.
- OK, then.

09:04.211 --> 09:07.755
How about we start
with the chateau in Bordeaux?

09:07.756 --> 09:09.298
- She can have it,

09:09.299 --> 09:14.804
that and any other properties
she wants.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.430
I want to discuss Elizabeth.

09:16.431 --> 09:19.350
- As you know, my client
intends to move back to London.

09:19.351 --> 09:21.686
- Elizabeth is
staying in Metropolis.

09:21.687 --> 09:22.979
- Over my dead body.

09:22.980 --> 09:24.480
- She's lived here
her entire life.

09:24.481 --> 09:26.315
I am not letting you take her
to some other country.

09:26.316 --> 09:28.401
- It's England.
- She's my daughter.

09:28.402 --> 09:30.987
- Who I don't want to expose
to this life anymore.

09:30.988 --> 09:33.489
All the crime accusations,

09:33.490 --> 09:35.658
constantly being trailed
by the feds--

09:35.659 --> 09:37.451
it is no way to live.

09:37.452 --> 09:40.913
Best thing for her is to be as
far away from you as possible.

09:40.914 --> 09:42.164
- I have given her everything.

09:42.165 --> 09:43.416
- Except love.

09:43.417 --> 09:45.960
- Don't you dare
say that to me!

09:45.961 --> 09:47.712
- Elizabeth.

09:47.713 --> 09:49.839
You weren't supposed to be home
for another hour.

09:49.840 --> 09:52.842
<i>[somber music]</i>

09:52.843 --> 09:56.178
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:56.179 --> 09:57.763
[door slams]

09:57.764 --> 09:59.641
- We're not done here.

10:01.643 --> 10:04.687
- So you think we should
say something to Mom and Dad?

10:04.688 --> 10:06.188
- Pretty sure
they've got bigger things

10:06.189 --> 10:07.481
going on right now.

10:07.482 --> 10:08.899
- Yeah, but Dad's been
keeping this secret

10:08.900 --> 10:10.234
pretty much his whole life,

10:10.235 --> 10:11.944
and now it's kind of just
getting out there.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.321
- It's only Denise.

10:13.322 --> 10:14.864
- And that Chuck Arden guy.

10:14.865 --> 10:17.325
- Look, I'm just saying,
Dad's still not totally super.

10:17.326 --> 10:18.534
And it's not like

10:18.535 --> 10:20.119
the "Daily Planet" knows
or anything.

10:20.120 --> 10:22.288
Probably best
not to freak him out.

10:22.289 --> 10:23.664
- You're probably right.

10:23.665 --> 10:25.166
<i>[pulsating]</i>

10:25.167 --> 10:27.126
Candice's bus is almost here.

10:27.127 --> 10:29.754
[phone vibrating]

10:29.755 --> 10:31.213
- Mom?

10:31.214 --> 10:34.759
Yeah, she should be
pulling up any second.

10:34.760 --> 10:38.054
Right now? Really?

10:38.055 --> 10:39.638
OK. OK.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.682
OK. Yes, OK.

10:41.683 --> 10:42.933
Dude, Mom needs me.

10:42.934 --> 10:44.560
It's an emergency.
Can you cover?

10:44.561 --> 10:46.312
- You're leaving me?

10:46.313 --> 10:48.022
- Dad's busy,
and you wanted time away

10:48.023 --> 10:50.483
from the whole hero thing,
so yeah.

10:50.484 --> 10:52.360
Just take Candice
back to the house.

10:52.361 --> 10:53.819
I'll be home
as soon as possible.

10:53.820 --> 10:55.446
- I don't even have my license!

10:55.447 --> 10:58.158
- Hands at 10:00 and 2:00,
and use your turn signal.

10:59.451 --> 11:02.662
[brakes squealing]

11:07.793 --> 11:09.168
- Jordan.
[laughs]

11:09.169 --> 11:10.294
- Hi, Candice.

11:10.295 --> 11:12.046
- It's so good to see you.

11:12.047 --> 11:13.464
I missed you.

11:13.465 --> 11:14.256
- You too.

11:14.257 --> 11:15.716
- I've wanted to visit,

11:15.717 --> 11:17.718
but Jon's been so busy
the past few weeks.

11:17.719 --> 11:18.928
- Yeah.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.763
- Where is he?
[chuckles]

11:20.764 --> 11:24.475
- He, uh, had to help my mom
with this big story.

11:24.476 --> 11:26.644
- Jon's helping her
at the paper now?

11:26.645 --> 11:29.230
- Yeah, he has that
reporter's DNA in his blood.

11:29.231 --> 11:33.401
- Mm, he never
mentioned that before.

11:33.402 --> 11:34.360
- Weird.

11:34.361 --> 11:35.986
That's--that's all your stuff?

11:35.987 --> 11:36.987
- Oh, yeah.

11:36.988 --> 11:39.115
- OK.

11:39.116 --> 11:41.492
- Thank you.

11:41.493 --> 11:43.161
- Yeah.

11:45.622 --> 11:47.957
- Wait, are you driving now?

11:47.958 --> 11:49.667
- We'll see.
- Oh.

11:49.668 --> 11:51.710
[bell tolls]

11:51.711 --> 11:53.713
[whooshes]

11:56.174 --> 11:57.299
- Is that her?

11:57.300 --> 11:59.219
- Yes. Stay here.

12:01.888 --> 12:02.972
<i>- Voilà, Madame.</i>

12:02.973 --> 12:04.641
<i>- Merci.</i>

12:07.394 --> 12:09.563
- Elizabeth Luthor.

12:12.315 --> 12:13.607
- Lois Lane.

12:13.608 --> 12:15.484
- I'm sorry
to surprise you like this.

12:15.485 --> 12:17.778
- Your dad promised
no one would ever find me.

12:17.779 --> 12:20.156
- Nobody else knows
where you are.

12:20.157 --> 12:21.824
- Where's General Lane?

12:21.825 --> 12:25.494
<i>[somber music]</i>

12:25.495 --> 12:29.123
My father.

12:29.124 --> 12:30.750
He found out.

12:33.462 --> 12:34.837
- You're pregnant.

12:34.838 --> 12:36.380
- Something I don't want him
to know about.

12:36.381 --> 12:37.798
Now, just leave me alone.

12:37.799 --> 12:39.467
- Please,
I have no other choice.

12:39.468 --> 12:40.968
Your father is trying
to destroy my family.

12:40.969 --> 12:42.261
- Then you need
to go into hiding.

12:42.262 --> 12:44.096
- That is not an option for us.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.223
I have two boys. They're 16.

12:46.224 --> 12:47.516
They mean everything to me.

12:47.517 --> 12:49.310
All I want to do
is keep them safe.

12:49.311 --> 12:51.395
- I don't know
how you expect me to help.

12:51.396 --> 12:52.897
- If you could
just talk to him.

12:52.898 --> 12:55.900
You are the one person
in the world he cares about.

12:55.901 --> 13:02.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:02.032 --> 13:03.908
- I haven't seen him in ages.

13:03.909 --> 13:07.995
- He still carries around
a picture of you.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.789
The one from Met Prep.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.292
- He used to walk me to school
almost every day,

13:13.293 --> 13:17.338
even the day he was--

13:17.339 --> 13:19.673
- I was wrong about Boss Moxie.

13:19.674 --> 13:22.259
- But you weren't wrong about
him being a criminal, were you?

13:22.260 --> 13:24.303
- No.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.055
- Then have him arrested
for one of his other crimes.

13:26.056 --> 13:27.389
- It's not that simple.

13:27.390 --> 13:29.643
- But having me talk to him is?

13:30.852 --> 13:32.228
I'm sorry.

13:32.229 --> 13:34.438
I can't have him in my life,
not with a child.

13:34.439 --> 13:36.232
- You went to my father
asking for help,

13:36.233 --> 13:38.943
and now I'm asking
the same of you.

13:38.944 --> 13:40.528
- Ms. Lane, please.

13:40.529 --> 13:42.321
- If there were any other way,
I wouldn't be here.

13:42.322 --> 13:43.906
But if you don't
talk to him soon,

13:43.907 --> 13:46.493
he is going to do something
terrible to my family.

13:54.584 --> 13:55.793
- You went to see
Luthor's daughter?

13:55.794 --> 13:57.253
- Well, after what you said
this morning,

13:57.254 --> 13:59.088
I thought she might be
our best chance

13:59.089 --> 14:00.756
to appeal to Luthor's heart.

14:00.757 --> 14:02.258
- Well, did she agree
to speak with him?

14:02.259 --> 14:04.176
- Not yet,
but she's considering.

14:04.177 --> 14:06.596
Turns out she's almost
six months pregnant.

14:08.390 --> 14:09.974
- Lex Luthor's
gonna be a grandfather.

14:09.975 --> 14:11.350
- I know.

14:11.351 --> 14:14.979
But, Clark,
we are running out of options.

14:14.980 --> 14:17.064
Maybe it's time for you
to go to the Fortress.

14:17.065 --> 14:18.732
- I'm not gonna leave
you and the boys.

14:18.733 --> 14:20.651
- You might have to.
That thing killed you.

14:20.652 --> 14:23.112
We can't go through that again.
I cannot go through that again.

14:23.113 --> 14:25.281
- And what if Luthor sends it
after you instead?

14:25.282 --> 14:27.449
- He would have
done that already.

14:27.450 --> 14:30.327
- I can't.
I can't just hide.

14:30.328 --> 14:32.746
- Sweetheart,
you are nowhere near ready.

14:32.747 --> 14:36.250
That thing is unlike anything
you have ever faced before.

14:36.251 --> 14:38.460
- Well, it is now.

14:38.461 --> 14:40.296
But it used to be me
on that other world,

14:40.297 --> 14:43.173
before Luthor got to it.

14:43.174 --> 14:45.051
- Do you think
your mom can help?

14:49.264 --> 14:52.517
[phone ringing]

14:55.061 --> 14:57.396
Elizabeth?

14:57.397 --> 15:00.441
- The shelter is doing
this puppy adoption thing.

15:00.442 --> 15:03.819
And I needed to get the story
before it closed.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.404
- I just kind of thought
it would have been

15:05.405 --> 15:07.948
something bigger, you know?

15:07.949 --> 15:12.911
- Look, the rest of the day,
it's you and me.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.622
No more distractions.

15:14.623 --> 15:16.665
- We will be right there.

15:16.666 --> 15:18.417
- Oh, hey, Mrs. Lane.

15:18.418 --> 15:21.003
- Hey, Candice, I know you came
all this way to see Jonathan,

15:21.004 --> 15:22.588
but I need his help again.

15:22.589 --> 15:26.008
- Does this have something
to do with the shelter?

15:26.009 --> 15:28.093
- Jordan will explain.
We have to go.

15:28.094 --> 15:31.096
<i>[somber music]</i>

15:31.097 --> 15:33.515
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:33.516 --> 15:36.226
- This won't take long,
I promise.

15:36.227 --> 15:42.816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:42.817 --> 15:46.195
- Can you really explain that?

15:46.196 --> 15:48.113
- I killed it over and over.

15:48.114 --> 15:51.033
And every time,
it just came back to life.

15:51.034 --> 15:53.869
<i>- There's no precedent for
anything like that on Krypton.</i>

15:53.870 --> 15:55.829
<i>Are you certain
this being was once you?</i>

15:55.830 --> 15:57.414
- I could sense him in there.

15:57.415 --> 15:59.875
But whatever Luthor did,
it changed him.

15:59.876 --> 16:01.460
I've never faced
anything this powerful.

16:01.461 --> 16:03.253
<i>- I have yet
to encounter a being</i>

16:03.254 --> 16:06.131
<i>that exists without weakness,
Kal.</i>

16:06.132 --> 16:08.175
- You don't understand.

16:08.176 --> 16:10.552
Whenever I killed it,
it came back stronger.

16:10.553 --> 16:12.888
It's as if dying
made it more powerful.

16:12.889 --> 16:16.141
How am I supposed to defeat
something like that?

16:16.142 --> 16:20.897
<i>- Walk me through what happened
and we shall search for a way.</i>

16:25.485 --> 16:29.196
<i>Ready?</i>

16:29.197 --> 16:32.784
<i>Let us see
where things went wrong.</i>

16:35.537 --> 16:38.039
[device beeps]

16:39.290 --> 16:42.084
- Go.
- [growling]

16:42.085 --> 16:43.919
<i>- The fight started
at the farm.</i>

16:43.920 --> 16:45.921
<i>It grabbed me so fast
I couldn't even react.</i>

16:45.922 --> 16:47.131
<i>- Continue.</i>

16:47.132 --> 16:48.257
- [roaring]

16:48.258 --> 16:50.008
<i>- When we got to the subway,</i>

16:50.009 --> 16:51.427
<i>that's when I knew
I was in trouble.</i>

16:51.428 --> 16:52.846
- [roars]

16:56.307 --> 16:59.435
<i>- You must continue, Kal.</i>

16:59.436 --> 17:01.520
- Play that again.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.272
- [roaring]

17:03.273 --> 17:04.773
<i>- He overpowered me here.</i>

17:04.774 --> 17:06.859
<i>He was stronger, faster.</i>

17:06.860 --> 17:08.777
- [groans]

17:08.778 --> 17:10.612
<i>- And when I killed it,</i>

17:10.613 --> 17:12.573
<i>it just came back
more powerful.</i>

17:12.574 --> 17:14.533
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:14.534 --> 17:17.077
- [roaring]

17:17.078 --> 17:22.082
- It kept coming back
over and over, until finally--

17:22.083 --> 17:24.168
[device whirring]

17:24.169 --> 17:27.129
- [roaring]

17:27.130 --> 17:28.590
<i>- Enough!</i>

17:31.468 --> 17:32.968
<i>- Kal.</i>

17:32.969 --> 17:34.553
- I can't beat it.

17:34.554 --> 17:36.263
<i>- We can walk through it again.</i>

17:36.264 --> 17:40.309
- It'll end the same way.

17:40.310 --> 17:42.979
<i>- Do not give up hope, my son.</i>

17:45.231 --> 17:46.941
- I have to tell Lois.

17:49.194 --> 17:50.486
[phone rings]

17:50.487 --> 17:51.653
- Yes?

17:51.654 --> 17:53.989
<i>- Milton found Elizabeth.</i>

17:53.990 --> 17:55.240
- Where was she?

17:55.241 --> 17:56.492
<i>- It's not so much
where she was,</i>

17:56.493 --> 17:57.993
<i>but who she was with.</i>

17:57.994 --> 17:59.788
<i>Look.</i>

18:01.206 --> 18:04.249
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

18:04.250 --> 18:08.253
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:08.254 --> 18:10.589
[door slams]

18:10.590 --> 18:13.300
- Where's my daughter?

18:13.301 --> 18:16.846
- We were just about
to head over.

18:21.768 --> 18:23.770
- Hey, Dad.

18:31.945 --> 18:33.070
- I guess
you got through to her.

18:33.071 --> 18:34.738
- We'll see.

18:34.739 --> 18:36.240
But if they can't
work things out,

18:36.241 --> 18:37.407
how's plan B looking?

18:37.408 --> 18:39.201
- My mom ran a simulation.

18:39.202 --> 18:41.411
It's--it's not gonna work.

18:41.412 --> 18:43.038
- Maybe you just need
more time.

18:43.039 --> 18:44.873
Three weeks ago, you were dead.

18:44.874 --> 18:46.667
- And I'm still not
fully recovered.

18:46.668 --> 18:48.961
I mean, if I couldn't stop
that thing at my best,

18:48.962 --> 18:50.629
how am I supposed
to beat it now?

18:50.630 --> 18:52.047
- Well, then we better hope

18:52.048 --> 18:54.175
Elizabeth can get through
to him.

18:55.844 --> 18:59.097
[indistinct chatter]

19:03.810 --> 19:06.312
- 17 years.

19:09.023 --> 19:11.985
Feels like forever
and an instant, all at once.

19:18.658 --> 19:20.368
How far along are you?

19:21.494 --> 19:24.080
- Um, almost six months.

19:26.541 --> 19:27.583
- Who's the father?

19:27.584 --> 19:29.334
- You don't get to know that.

19:29.335 --> 19:32.337
<i>[somber music]</i>

19:32.338 --> 19:35.507
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:35.508 --> 19:37.677
- Why did you stop writing me?

19:39.470 --> 19:40.804
- That's what
you want to ask me?

19:40.805 --> 19:42.849
- Your letters were all I had.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.851
- I needed to put
everything behind me

19:45.852 --> 19:47.936
so that I could move on.

19:47.937 --> 19:50.273
- You mean move on from me.

19:53.902 --> 19:56.653
- Do you know how hard it was
to be your daughter?

19:56.654 --> 19:58.780
To grow up
with the last name Luthor?

19:58.781 --> 20:00.532
People found out who I was
and assumed the worst.

20:00.533 --> 20:02.660
They thought I was like you.

20:05.455 --> 20:07.164
- I didn't kill those people.

20:07.165 --> 20:09.625
- No.

20:09.626 --> 20:13.295
No, but you've done
other things,

20:13.296 --> 20:14.963
killed other people.

20:14.964 --> 20:18.258
- All lies,
lies spread by Lois Lane.

20:18.259 --> 20:20.469
- Don't make this about her.

20:20.470 --> 20:24.182
She's far from the only one
who believes you're a monster.

20:26.517 --> 20:28.019
- Do you?

20:31.564 --> 20:33.232
- I don't want to.

20:36.903 --> 20:41.323
- I've always shown you
who I am.

20:41.324 --> 20:43.158
Always.

20:43.159 --> 20:48.497
If there's anyone that knows
the real me,

20:48.498 --> 20:50.123
it's you.

20:50.124 --> 20:56.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:56.339 --> 20:59.341
[knock at door]

20:59.342 --> 21:00.842
Can we talk?

21:00.843 --> 21:08.142
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:15.024 --> 21:17.025
You shouldn't be
in the middle of this.

21:17.026 --> 21:20.696
- You and Mom always argue
about me.

21:20.697 --> 21:24.199
- No, no, this is about us,
not you.

21:24.200 --> 21:29.122
A lot went wrong
in our marriage.

21:31.207 --> 21:33.625
- Like what?

21:33.626 --> 21:37.296
- Well, for starters,
I wasn't ready.

21:42.969 --> 21:45.013
- Did you want to be a dad?

21:48.349 --> 21:51.936
- No, not at first.

21:55.898 --> 21:59.026
But then...

21:59.027 --> 22:02.904
I saw how much different
you were than me.

22:02.905 --> 22:06.909
You were so much better.

22:09.078 --> 22:14.708
You are the one good thing
I've done in my life.

22:14.709 --> 22:19.004
Everything else
was about survival.

22:19.005 --> 22:24.010
The reason I'm fighting
to be part of your life...

22:26.387 --> 22:28.764
Is because
you're the best part of mine.

22:28.765 --> 22:34.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:34.479 --> 22:38.774
- You're not the man
who sat with me in that closet.

22:38.775 --> 22:40.318
You never were.

22:45.448 --> 22:46.782
- You're wrong.

22:46.783 --> 22:51.204
Lil, all I want is the chance
to be your dad again.

22:52.872 --> 22:54.499
That's all I'm asking.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.417
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

22:57.418 --> 23:00.170
[laughter]

23:00.171 --> 23:03.965
- So there's some sort
of puppy adoption conspiracy?

23:03.966 --> 23:05.425
- Yeah, exactly.

23:05.426 --> 23:08.053
- And you're investigating it
with your mom?

23:08.054 --> 23:10.138
- Black market puppies
are big news.

23:10.139 --> 23:12.140
- Right, and we're not supposed
to talk about the story.

23:12.141 --> 23:13.642
- Wait,
that doesn't make sense.

23:13.643 --> 23:15.769
Why can't you talk about it?

23:15.770 --> 23:16.978
- Yo!

23:16.979 --> 23:18.355
- Look who decided to show up.

23:18.356 --> 23:20.232
- Supposed to be here
an hour ago.

23:20.233 --> 23:22.442
- Jon was busy covering
a big story with his mom.

23:22.443 --> 23:24.569
- I thought you were
a fireman or something.

23:24.570 --> 23:26.530
- [laughs]

23:26.531 --> 23:28.532
- OK, you're both lying to me.

23:28.533 --> 23:32.160
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:32.161 --> 23:35.330
- Uh, we're gonna go
check on the keg.

23:35.331 --> 23:41.878
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:41.879 --> 23:43.839
- Candice, just--
- No, just stop it, OK?

23:43.840 --> 23:45.550
Stop lying.

23:48.302 --> 23:49.678
If you didn't want me
to come here,

23:49.679 --> 23:51.179
you should have just told me.

23:51.180 --> 23:53.849
- No, no, I want you here
more than anything.

23:53.850 --> 23:55.684
- Then tell me
what's really going on,

23:55.685 --> 23:57.353
or I'm leaving.

24:02.567 --> 24:04.526
- I can't believe
you still have this.

24:04.527 --> 24:05.902
How old was I?

24:05.903 --> 24:07.989
- You had just turned 14.

24:11.784 --> 24:13.994
This is how you looked
the last time I saw you.

24:13.995 --> 24:15.203
- [chuckles]

24:15.204 --> 24:17.747
I look a little different now.

24:17.748 --> 24:19.624
- Sound a little different too.

24:19.625 --> 24:22.711
- My accent changed pretty soon
after we moved to England.

24:22.712 --> 24:26.715
I guess
I just wanted to fit in.

24:26.716 --> 24:28.301
- It suits you.

24:32.471 --> 24:35.098
I heard you went
to medical school.

24:35.099 --> 24:37.726
- Graduated top of my class.

24:37.727 --> 24:39.728
- I know.

24:39.729 --> 24:41.146
- Right.

24:41.147 --> 24:45.192
You had your PIs following me.

24:45.193 --> 24:47.861
- I was trying to understand
who you were becoming.

24:47.862 --> 24:50.155
- You could have asked Mom.
- I did.

24:50.156 --> 24:52.782
Your mother insisted
on keeping me in the dark.

24:52.783 --> 24:54.242
- Don't blame her.

24:54.243 --> 24:56.328
She's not the reason
you went to prison.

24:56.329 --> 25:00.541
- [chuckles]
No, that, that was Lois Lane.

25:01.918 --> 25:02.918
- What?

25:02.919 --> 25:04.211
- I told her she was wrong.

25:04.212 --> 25:05.921
She didn't listen.

25:05.922 --> 25:09.841
Instead, she took you
out of my life.

25:09.842 --> 25:12.302
- Lois Lane isn't to blame.

25:12.303 --> 25:14.554
It was the choices
that you made.

25:14.555 --> 25:17.057
You are the reason
I grew up without a father.

25:17.058 --> 25:19.392
- No, it was her.

25:19.393 --> 25:21.937
- [laughs]

25:21.938 --> 25:24.105
Even now,
you can't take responsibility.

25:24.106 --> 25:26.233
- Not for something
I didn't do.

25:26.234 --> 25:29.277
- It's always someone else's
fault, isn't it?

25:29.278 --> 25:30.570
- Lil--

25:30.571 --> 25:32.030
- No.

25:32.031 --> 25:34.075
This was a mistake.

25:35.993 --> 25:37.369
<i>- Something's happening.</i>

25:37.370 --> 25:38.620
- She's leaving.

25:38.621 --> 25:39.704
I'll talk to her.

25:39.705 --> 25:40.914
- Talking didn't work, Clark.

25:40.915 --> 25:42.457
He's gonna send that thing.

25:42.458 --> 25:44.293
- I will fix this.

25:48.172 --> 25:51.091
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:51.092 --> 25:54.386
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:54.387 --> 25:56.179
- Grandpa's ELT.

25:56.180 --> 25:57.931
- You think Granddad was here?
- No, but Luthor was.

25:57.932 --> 26:00.475
And my guess is, he used that
to call his new pet.

26:00.476 --> 26:07.608
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:11.946 --> 26:13.446
- Elizabeth?

26:13.447 --> 26:14.656
Elizabeth?

26:14.657 --> 26:18.159
Hi, I'm Clark Kent,
Lois Lane's husband.

26:18.160 --> 26:20.287
- Please, I just want
to go home.

26:20.288 --> 26:21.997
- And I can absolutely help
with that,

26:21.998 --> 26:25.458
if you just give me a minute.

26:25.459 --> 26:28.378
- I'm sorry my father's
coming after your family,

26:28.379 --> 26:31.006
but you have no idea
how hard this is for me.

26:31.007 --> 26:33.091
- And I won't pretend to.

26:33.092 --> 26:37.345
But I also lost my dad
when I was young,

26:37.346 --> 26:39.931
just a few years older
than you were.

26:39.932 --> 26:43.101
And there's not a day
that goes by

26:43.102 --> 26:45.770
that I don't miss him.

26:45.771 --> 26:50.191
- Well, I'm betting your father
was nothing like mine.

26:50.192 --> 26:52.193
Mine's a monster.

26:52.194 --> 26:54.321
- Was he always?

26:54.322 --> 26:57.866
Look, I think losing you
changed something in him.

26:57.867 --> 26:59.075
- Don't put this on me.

26:59.076 --> 27:00.994
It's not my job to fix him.

27:00.995 --> 27:02.370
- No, no, no, no, not at all.

27:02.371 --> 27:05.832
I--it's just,
you lost something too.

27:05.833 --> 27:10.337
And if you don't at least try
to get it back, I--

27:10.338 --> 27:12.381
I think you'll regret it.

27:22.975 --> 27:24.100
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

27:24.101 --> 27:25.935
<i>- ♪ I'm gonna hit the road ♪</i>

27:25.936 --> 27:27.270
[laughter]

27:27.271 --> 27:28.396
- OK, where were you?

27:28.397 --> 27:29.856
- It's not what you think.

27:29.857 --> 27:32.359
- Then just tell me.
Like, why is that so hard?

27:32.360 --> 27:33.985
- Look, there's things
going on right now

27:33.986 --> 27:36.279
that I can't talk about.

27:36.280 --> 27:39.491
Look, I'm not trying
to hide anything.

27:39.492 --> 27:41.284
- I'm--I'm done.

27:41.285 --> 27:43.411
<i>[somber music]</i>

27:43.412 --> 27:44.621
- Whoa.

27:44.622 --> 27:46.790
I can't imagine
hiding that secret.

27:46.791 --> 27:50.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:50.127 --> 27:52.087
Does Sarah know?

27:52.088 --> 27:53.338
- I should probably go talk
to my brother.

27:53.339 --> 27:55.715
- Yeah, yeah, for sure.

27:55.716 --> 27:58.344
[bell rings]
- Have a good night.

28:22.201 --> 28:25.120
<i>[gentle music]</i>

28:25.121 --> 28:32.461
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:35.423 --> 28:38.175
- I tried to be
a good father, Lil.

28:40.886 --> 28:42.930
Wanted to break the cycle.

28:45.433 --> 28:48.143
The first time my father
walked out on me and my mother,

28:48.144 --> 28:49.978
I was seven.

28:49.979 --> 28:52.564
[both grunting]

28:52.565 --> 28:56.151
<i>He didn't want
to raise some kid.</i>

28:56.152 --> 29:00.573
My mother,
she hated him for it.

29:02.992 --> 29:05.202
She took that anger out on me.

29:06.245 --> 29:08.621
<i>Used his own belt</i>

29:08.622 --> 29:11.625
<i>because it was the one thing
he left behind.</i>

29:12.751 --> 29:14.711
And the abuse didn't stop
until I left

29:14.712 --> 29:17.298
and learned to take care
of myself.

29:18.591 --> 29:21.384
- I never heard any of this.

29:21.385 --> 29:23.721
- It's better you didn't.

29:27.433 --> 29:29.309
You were too perfect.

29:29.310 --> 29:33.188
- [exhales]
Dad.

29:33.189 --> 29:35.273
- Being in Stryker's,
the hardest part

29:35.274 --> 29:39.486
wasn't being locked up.

29:39.487 --> 29:41.905
It was wondering
if you needed me.

29:41.906 --> 29:43.782
- [sighs]

29:47.119 --> 29:48.495
[sniffles]

29:48.496 --> 29:50.788
I did.

29:50.789 --> 29:53.959
- I should have been there
to take care of you.

29:57.796 --> 29:59.798
Please, Lil...

30:02.510 --> 30:04.344
Let me be there now.

30:04.345 --> 30:11.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:15.940 --> 30:17.273
<i>- How could you do this?</i>

30:17.274 --> 30:19.567
She is a 14-year-old girl.

30:19.568 --> 30:21.528
- So?
- So she's not old enough

30:21.529 --> 30:23.196
to know that this is
a terrible idea.

30:23.197 --> 30:25.740
- Mom, yes, I am.

30:25.741 --> 30:29.452
I want to live here with Dad.

30:29.453 --> 30:34.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:34.750 --> 30:36.209
- You just want me to suffer.

30:36.210 --> 30:37.752
- I didn't ask her to choose.

30:37.753 --> 30:39.462
- You punish anyone
who gets in your way,

30:39.463 --> 30:41.381
no matter the consequence.

30:41.382 --> 30:46.261
I just pray Elizabeth sees
who you really are

30:46.262 --> 30:48.096
before it's too late.

30:48.097 --> 30:55.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:59.900 --> 31:02.819
<i>[ominous music]</i>

31:02.820 --> 31:09.952
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:21.213 --> 31:22.715
- OK.

31:34.852 --> 31:36.812
This has to work.

31:40.316 --> 31:41.983
All right.

31:41.984 --> 31:44.986
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

31:44.987 --> 31:48.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:48.073 --> 31:51.659
[device whirring]

31:51.660 --> 31:53.870
- That looked really rough.

31:53.871 --> 31:56.372
You doing all right?

31:56.373 --> 31:57.915
- I don't know.

31:57.916 --> 32:01.169
I think Candice wants
to go back to her aunt's.

32:01.170 --> 32:03.046
- You gonna take her?

32:03.047 --> 32:04.547
- I guess so.

32:04.548 --> 32:07.175
<i>[distant whirring]</i>

32:07.176 --> 32:08.343
- That's Granddad's ELT.

32:08.344 --> 32:11.721
- It must be Mom.
- You should go.

32:11.722 --> 32:14.223
Don't worry,
I'll take care of Candice.

32:14.224 --> 32:21.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:25.110 --> 32:27.528
[whooshes]

32:27.529 --> 32:29.030
- What are you doing here?

32:29.031 --> 32:30.198
- You hit Grandpa's ELT.

32:30.199 --> 32:31.908
- No, baby, you have to leave.

32:31.909 --> 32:34.202
- What's going on?
- You have to leave right now.

32:34.203 --> 32:36.371
[rumbling]

32:36.372 --> 32:39.708
- [roaring]

32:46.298 --> 32:47.840
- [roars]

32:47.841 --> 32:48.800
- Come on.

32:48.801 --> 32:50.551
We need to go.
- Stay back.

32:50.552 --> 32:53.221
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:53.222 --> 32:57.475
- [roars]

32:57.476 --> 32:59.894
- Listen to me.

32:59.895 --> 33:01.104
- Mom?

33:01.105 --> 33:03.272
- [growling]

33:03.273 --> 33:05.609
- I've seen it in your eyes.

33:08.362 --> 33:10.154
You know me.

33:10.155 --> 33:13.158
- [growling]

33:14.159 --> 33:18.913
- Just look at me
and try to remember.

33:18.914 --> 33:23.376
- [snarling]

33:23.377 --> 33:26.587
[panting]

33:26.588 --> 33:28.923
- You know me.

33:28.924 --> 33:31.259
- [growls]

33:31.260 --> 33:35.180
[panting]

33:40.144 --> 33:43.020
- What's happening?

33:43.021 --> 33:44.690
- I was right.

33:45.649 --> 33:47.860
- A grandson.

33:49.069 --> 33:50.154
[chuckles]

33:53.532 --> 33:55.116
With you, I--

33:55.117 --> 33:56.534
I had hoped for a girl.

33:56.535 --> 33:58.077
- Well, we are thrilled.

33:58.078 --> 34:01.122
My husband is the youngest
of five, all girls.

34:01.123 --> 34:02.373
He painted the nursery blue

34:02.374 --> 34:04.876
the week we found out
I was pregnant.

34:04.877 --> 34:07.962
- You're gonna be
a great mother.

34:07.963 --> 34:11.257
- Did you ever think
about being a grandfather?

34:11.258 --> 34:12.508
- Hmm.

34:12.509 --> 34:15.887
Growing up where I did,

34:15.888 --> 34:18.097
I didn't think
I'd be around this long.

34:18.098 --> 34:21.268
- South Metropolis has changed
a lot since then.

34:22.603 --> 34:25.272
How is it now that you're back?

34:27.065 --> 34:31.194
- I haven't been
to Metropolis much yet.

34:31.195 --> 34:34.447
<i>[somber music]</i>

34:34.448 --> 34:37.325
- You've been here?
- That's right.

34:37.326 --> 34:38.451
- In this town?

34:38.452 --> 34:43.539
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:43.540 --> 34:45.250
Because of Lois Lane?

34:52.049 --> 34:53.841
So it's true.

34:53.842 --> 34:56.762
You're trying
to destroy her family.

34:59.348 --> 35:01.599
- She told you that?

35:01.600 --> 35:05.019
That's why you came to see me.

35:05.020 --> 35:09.357
Lois Lane took
17 years of my life.

35:09.358 --> 35:10.817
- Which you could
never get back.

35:10.818 --> 35:13.027
- There has to be a price!

35:13.028 --> 35:20.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:24.122 --> 35:28.334
- Not if you want to be
in my life

35:28.335 --> 35:31.797
or your grandson's.

35:35.676 --> 35:38.678
All those years ago,

35:38.679 --> 35:41.430
I chose you.

35:41.431 --> 35:44.184
And now it's your turn.

35:48.605 --> 35:50.816
Choose me.

35:53.735 --> 35:54.902
- Don't do this, Elizabeth.

35:54.903 --> 35:56.654
- If you truly want
to break the cycle,

35:56.655 --> 35:58.990
you'll leave this all behind.

35:58.991 --> 36:03.036
Please, it--
it's the only way, Dad.

36:09.126 --> 36:10.418
- She has to pay.

36:10.419 --> 36:17.759
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:19.636 --> 36:23.306
- [sighs]

36:23.307 --> 36:25.726
Mom was right about you.

36:33.317 --> 36:37.945
I won't expose my son
to this kind of hatred.

36:37.946 --> 36:41.616
So stay out of my life...

36:41.617 --> 36:43.367
forever.

36:43.368 --> 36:50.709
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:58.300 --> 37:01.218
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:01.219 --> 37:08.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:14.733 --> 37:17.235
<i>- You have a great day.</i>

37:19.738 --> 37:21.822
- The concert's
right after last period.

37:21.823 --> 37:23.157
Doors open at 4:00.

37:23.158 --> 37:24.325
- I'll be there.

37:24.326 --> 37:25.827
[air whooshes]

37:28.080 --> 37:29.373
- Dad?

37:32.292 --> 37:34.336
- I love you, Lil.

37:36.004 --> 37:38.172
Head inside before you're late.

37:38.173 --> 37:45.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:53.021 --> 37:56.232
In front of my daughter,

37:56.233 --> 37:58.693
at her school?

37:58.694 --> 38:00.736
- The police agreed
to let me bring you in

38:00.737 --> 38:02.113
so you could say goodbye.

38:02.114 --> 38:04.073
- I told Lois
I didn't kill Moxie.

38:04.074 --> 38:05.574
- The evidence says otherwise.

38:05.575 --> 38:08.954
- You and Lois Lane are
destroying my family.

38:10.998 --> 38:13.290
I will never forget this.

38:13.291 --> 38:20.382
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:23.468 --> 38:25.429
[phone vibrates]

38:36.023 --> 38:38.941
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

38:38.942 --> 38:42.195
[indistinct chatter]

38:45.490 --> 38:47.325
- Hey, I'm happy to take--

38:48.577 --> 38:50.077
Uh, what's happening?

38:50.078 --> 38:52.955
- Jordan told me everything.

38:52.956 --> 38:56.292
- Can you narrow down
"everything"?

38:56.293 --> 39:00.338
- About your dad
and who he really is.

39:01.548 --> 39:03.591
About you and Jordan.

39:03.592 --> 39:06.385
- That everything.
- Mm-hmm, that everything.

39:06.386 --> 39:08.054
- Right.

39:08.055 --> 39:10.807
- You know, you're lucky
to have such a sweet brother.

39:12.684 --> 39:16.312
- Yeah, he's OK.

39:16.313 --> 39:17.980
- Fire in the hole!

39:17.981 --> 39:19.774
<i>- ♪ Messing around ♪</i>

39:19.775 --> 39:22.777
[fireworks whistling]

39:22.778 --> 39:25.780
[all cheering]

39:25.781 --> 39:33.121
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:34.372 --> 39:38.085
<i>♪ Try and use it now ♪</i>

39:43.131 --> 39:46.300
- Lois, Elizabeth left
and she's not coming back.

39:46.301 --> 39:48.928
We have to get the boys
and go to the Fortress.

39:48.929 --> 39:51.556
- Sit down and watch
the fireworks with me.

39:52.808 --> 39:54.558
- Lois, Luthor is gonna send
his monster.

39:54.559 --> 39:55.559
We are not safe here.

39:55.560 --> 39:57.394
- Yes, we are.

39:57.395 --> 40:00.898
We don't have to worry
about that thing anymore.

40:00.899 --> 40:02.608
<i>- What'd you do?</i>

40:02.609 --> 40:05.611
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:05.612 --> 40:10.783
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:10.784 --> 40:12.201
<i>- I realized we were trying</i>

40:12.202 --> 40:14.286
<i>to get through
to the wrong heart.</i>

40:14.287 --> 40:21.419
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:22.963 --> 40:25.756
- [growling]

40:25.757 --> 40:27.842
- On your world,
you were married.

40:27.843 --> 40:29.051
- [growls]

40:29.052 --> 40:33.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:33.890 --> 40:35.558
- On your world,
you had a family.

40:35.559 --> 40:38.644
- [snarls]

40:38.645 --> 40:40.688
- I know you lost that family.

40:40.689 --> 40:42.941
- [growls]

40:44.359 --> 40:46.527
- And I know
how much that hurt.

40:46.528 --> 40:49.029
- [breathing heavily]

40:49.030 --> 40:52.491
- But destroying mine
won't ever bring yours back.

40:52.492 --> 40:56.996
Please, whatever Luthor
has asked of you,

40:56.997 --> 41:00.749
don't hurt my family.

41:00.750 --> 41:04.087
- [breathing heavily]

41:07.465 --> 41:10.217
[roars]

41:10.218 --> 41:11.719
[yells]

41:11.720 --> 41:19.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:27.819 --> 41:29.695
- Someone called for it.

41:29.696 --> 41:32.991
<i>- [growling]</i>

41:37.037 --> 41:44.294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:54.221 --> 41:57.139
<i>[heroic music]</i>

41:57.140 --> 42:04.481
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:14.366 --> 42:16.576
- Greg, move your head.
